Author: Dr. Meshal Alawein
Email: meshal@berkeley.edu
Institution: University of California, Berkeley
Research Focus: Computational Physics & Materials Modeling

This software was developed as part of research in nanomagnetic logic devices
and computational micromagnetism at UC Berkeley. The work reproduces and extends
results from published peer-reviewed research in the field of spintronics and
magnetic computing devices.

For academic use, please cite the original research papers:
- M. Alawein et al., "Multistate nanomagnetic logic using equilateral permalloy 
  triangles," IEEE Magnetics Letters, vol. 10, pp. 1-5, 2019.
  DOI: 10.1109/LMAG.2019.2912398

Third-party components included in this software are subject to their own licenses:
- OOMMF: NIST Public License (https://math.nist.gov/oommf/LICENSE.html)
- MuMax3: GPL v3 License (https://mumax.github.io/)
- Scientific Python libraries: Various OSI-approved licenses (see requirements.txt)